-- U.S. RESEARCH ROUNDUP-BlackBerry, Xilinx, Sandisk
-- 
-- Mon Mar 31, 2014 05:10AM EDT
-- None



March 31 (Reuters) - Wall Street securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several U.S.-listed companies, including BlackBerry, Xilinx and Sandisk, on Monday.

HIGHLIGHTS * BlackBerry <BBRY.O>: Evercore cuts to underweight; Canaccord Genuity, UBS up target price  * Sandisk <SNDK.O>: Morgan Stanley raises target price to $82 from $78   Following is a summary of research actions on U.S. companies reported by Reuters on Monday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* Amdocs Ltd <DOX.O>: Oppenheimer raises price target to $52 from $47; rating outperform * BlackBerry <BBRY.O>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price to $8 from $6; rating hold * BlackBerry <BBRY.O>: UBS raises target price to $8.50 from $8; rating neutral * BlackBerry <BBRY.O>: Evercore cuts to underweight from equal-weight rating  * BlackBerry <BBRY.O>: Evercore cuts target price to $6 from $7 * Carrizo Oil & Gas, Inc. <CRZO.O>: Jefferies raises target price to $49; rating hold  * Cavium <CAVM.O>: Morgan Stanley raises target price to $52 from $48; rating overweight * Cellular Dynamics <ICEL.O>: Cowen And Company cuts target to $18 from $20.50; outperform * Edison International <EIX.N>: Jefferies raises target price to $61 from $51; rating hold * Express Scripts Holding Co <ESRX.O>: Jefferies raises target to $86 from $84; rating buy * Kinross Gold <KGC.N>: RBC cuts target price to $7 from $7.50; rating outperform * Leidos Holdings Inc <LDOS.N>: JP Morgan cuts price target to $40 from $46; rating neutral * Nucor Corp <NUE.N>: KeyBanc cuts price target to $58 from $59; buy rating * Penn Virginia <PVA.N>: Jefferies raises target price to $22; rating buy * Sandisk <SNDK.O>: Morgan Stanley raises target price to $82 from $78; rating equal-weight  * Voxeljet AG <VJET.N>: Jefferies cuts price target to $27 from $40; rating hold